- [ ] No macro system. We will have some meta staging from the meta
      language. Paper: https://dl.acm.org/doi/pdf/10.1145/258993.259019
- [ ] User defined compile time directives as attributes.
- [ ] Exposure of compiler plugin meaning the user can create event pull
      based compiler plugins instead of jai's message push style one.

- [x] Alloca does not take into account for function frame so if a function returns multiple returns
      Fix stack allocation to allocate new memory depeding of the stack frame slot provided by the function.

- [x] Not emit obj and asm crap in the same dir put it in its own separate userspace directory.

2026:07:23 Idea masturbation
- [ ] Array declaration as literal should work since type inference knows the types at compile type.
  ```
  xs : []i32 = { 33, 44, 77 }; // Such code should be valid.
  ```

- [ ] Implement type system of standard-ml(moscow ml: https://mosml.org/). Meaning as if var declaration can not
  just take offset with implicit conversion of the same family class. This is for type saftey instead of always casting
  stuff and changing how they are loaded into register.

- [x] Use blocks for SSA ir.

## Arrays

- [ ] Fix type indexer to not allow indexing of invalid size at compile time.
  ```
  xs : []i32 = { 33, 44, 77 }; // Such code should be valid.
  f := xs[222]; // This should automatically be an error as the count of xs is 3.
  ```

- [ ] Array should have pointer .len to get the count of the array aka the element count.
- [ ] Slicing into arrays like xs[2..] or xs[..3] should they be allowed(TBD)??
- [ ] For looping over arr to do the element should be possible.
  ```
  array : []u32 = { 22, 33, 44 };
  for arr: array {
      printf("%d\n", arr);
  }
  ```
  If at any given moment we want to index over it.
  ```
  for it: 0..array.len {
      printf("%d %d\n", it, arr[it]);
  }
  ```

- [ ] Array in strcuture or other declaration is not supported they should be supported.
